Nairobi Basketball Association (NBA) finals throws off this weekend at the Upper Hill School courts. According to NBA fixtures secretary Caleb Osewe, the games will for the first time be played on the best of seven series.  Mustangs will take on Woodley Knights in the men’s semi-finals while University of Nairobi ‘Dynamites’, the only unbeaten side so far, will entertain Safe Spaces in the women’s match. In the classification games, Allstars play Slum Dunk Academy while Riara University Ladies meet Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology. The winners in the two categories will get a direct ticket to the Kenya Basketball Federation (KBF) lower division while the runners up will qualify for the inter provincial championships in Kisii next month. The trophy presentation will be done at the Railways Club as soon as the season is completed.